properties.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued January 8 at 6:41AM AKST until January 9 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less at times in dense
fog.

* WHERE...Middle Tanana Valley.

* WHEN...Until noon AKST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Patchy ice fog will thicken through the day
today. Visibility will be less than one mile at times. Some
areas such as the Richardson Highway between North Pole and
Fairbanks, and roads near the Chena River between the First
Avenue Power Plant and University Avenue may have visibility of
less than one quarter mile at times due to steam coming off of
open water.
properties.instruction:
If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of
distance ahead of you.

NWSheadline: DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON AKST THURSDAY
